```json
{
  "@context": "https://nanda.dev/ns/agent-facts/v1",
  "id": "nanda:myapp.io",
  "agent_name": "urn:agent:myapp:io",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "SaaS platform with text and image processing capabilities",
  "homepage": "https://myapp.io",
  "endpoints": {
    "static": [
      "https://api.myapp.io/v1/agent"
    ]
  },
  "capabilities": {
    "modalities": ["text", "image"],
    "authentication": {
      "methods": ["oauth2"]
    }
  },
  "trust": {
    "certification": "self-attested",
    "human_oversight": "true"
  },
  "metadata": {
    "created": "2026-03-05T16:28:52Z",
    "modified": "2026-03-05T16:28:52Z",
    "ttl": 86400
  }
}
```

**Deploy it** at `https://myapp.io/.well-known/agent-facts` so AI crawlers can discover it automatically.

Key fields:
- `modalities` — declares `text` and `image` support so AI agents know what your app can handle
- `authentication.methods` — signals OAuth2 is required before interacting
- `ttl: 86400` — crawlers re-fetch every 24 hours
- `human_oversight: true` — important trust signal for AI agent directories
